To engage: simply insert the Key into the button on the rear or side of the pistol and rotate one-quarter turn clockwise. This engages the Security System. The manual safety cannot be moved and the trigger cannot be pulled. To disengage: simply rotate the key one-quarter turn back. This releases the Security System, yet leaves the pistol's manual safety in the "safe" position until you are ready to release it yourself and fire the gun.

Everything works like new, so if you just want a great squirrel or rabbit gun with some history, this will make you happy.

I present the Daniel Defense DDM4 V5 M4 Carbine Mil-Spec Rifle system. Below is a link giving the specifics of this same rifle for sale (except the stock). The rifle is 100% factory installed, not a "parts gun". Daniel Defense is widely considered the premier MIL SPEC AR15/M4 platforms being made. 

https://danieldefense.com/firearms/mid-length/daniel-defense-m4-carbine-v5.html

I purchased and added on to this rifle after doing many months of research on creating the "perfect weapon system" for any defensive/offensive situation in virtually any scenario that would come up. ONLY reason I am selling is because I am saving up for a full auto, so my baby has to go...

As part of building this weapon system, I chose the:

-Daniel Defense M4 Carbine because it kept popping up in list after list of the "best of the best" because of its durability, attention to detail/quality, and adherence to Military Specifications/tolerances. Watch this video on YouTube and you'll see why the DDM4 is the best M4/AR15 on the market from a durability standpoint http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y1kX0nCEh5E

-Burris MTAC Ballistic CQ/LR (Close Quarter/Long Range) tactical optic because it offers both Close Quarters and Medium/Long Range capabilities in the same platform and the same time. Using "true 1x" it allows for both eyes open use (just like a red dot...AimPoint for example), and up to 4x magnification with built in 5.56 BDC reticles for effective engagements up to 600 yards. Just zero for 100 yards (which it already is) and your ready to go out to 600 yards using the built in BDC dots. It is extremely clear, has illuminated reticle (which work even if the battery dies), weather and shock proof, with a lifetime warranty. It is just like having both a Red Dot and a Tactical magnified scope in one, giving you the best of both worlds in one small, lightweight package.

-5.11 LED Tactical Lightweight High Output Weapons light because of it's superior performance inside of an extremely light frame. It is weather/shock proof with high, low, and strobe capabilities. Mounts perfect along side the foregrip for easy of use in any conditions.

-45 degree backup sight for obvious reasons; just in case something were to happen the MTAC optic this rifle can still be effective at close and medium/long ranges.

-Viking VTAC battle sling after much research in the best sling for all situations. Check out how awesome this sling is here: 
http://www.vikingtactics.com/product-p/vtac-mk2.htm

-Quick detach Harris bipod. Small and compact, but adjustable and sturdy. Can be added/removed to the M4 very quickly if the situation requires it. Quickly turns this M4 from a close quarters machine into a medium/long tactical precision weapon. 

Comes with everything listed above, plus:

Hard Carrying case, (4) 30 round mags, 90 rounds of ammo, scope lenses covers, and original boxes for most accessories.

I have well over $2500 invested in this barely used and meticulously cleaned piece of art. Price - $2000 OBO. You will NOT regret taking this beauty home. Please be realistic with your offers or they will be ignored.

The CH was stamped on barrels at Tula to be used as sniper rifles, but some were not drilled.  Why no one is sure, but the most likely thought is that they had more barrels than they needed.  

Rifle is in overall fair shape cosmetically.  It is un-refinished and as such has a good deal of finish wear.  The stock is fair condition with a couple of cracks and field repairs (brass nails).  The side of the stock was carved at some point with an OH.  Barrel is fair to good condition and has been counterbored.  bolt, receiver and barrel all match, floor plate and butt plate do not.   Comes with sling and bayonet.  

Cash or cashiers check only.  No low ball offers. No trades unless you have an early Honda Goldwing, then lets talk :)

title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 64 Carbine 30 WCF Lyman 56 1935
postcontent: Offered for your consideration is a fine early model 64 carbine made in 1935. Factory correct 20 inch carbine barrel with integral front sight ramp, bore is sharp and mirror bright. The barrell and magazine retain 95% original blue. The receiver is mechanically fine, feeds, fires and ejects smoothly. Headspace is perfect. Receiver has the typical mottled finish from this era, the carbona blue just never held that well on the nickle steel Winchester used in the receivers. It has the Lyman 56 receiver sight which was a factory option. The wood is solid and tight, nicely grained black walnut that has a few very minor handling marks but no chips, cracks, extra holes or bad dents. This is a fine vintage Winchester that has that "slick as glass" feel when you cycle the bolt. A rare model 64 factory carbine from an era of fine craftmanship we will probably never see again.

title: For Sale:  Monster Pasture Raised Turkeys - Frozen and ready for Thanksgiving
postcontent:
Got a BIG crew to feed on Thanksgiving? Have I got some birds for you!

These birds were raised on pasture so in addition to high quality poultry feed they ate such turkey delicacies as clover, dandelions, mulberries , choke cherries, crickets and grass hoppers.

They spent days outside in the sun moving around and their nights roosting on an old swing set. They had a nice shed to sleep in which they refuse to use, stupid birds. Anyway what this means is you get a bird with more flavor than your basic store bought turkey. The dark meat will be darker and the bird will overall be less salty since its not injected with salt water.

This years birds are Broad Breasted Bronze so theyre going to run a little bigger than last years birds. They will have bigger breast more like a grocery store bird, but with more flavor. They'll come to you professionally butchered and frozen. Quite a bit like you get from the store. You'll get the neck and giblets for your gravy or for the dog.
